caption: Excellent, flavorful sandwiches.

I’ve been wanting to try this place for a while and finally got around to doing so. We ordered the picnic for two. The guy behind the register seemed either high or he had literally never looked at the menu before in his life. Like first day of work status but with very slow reaction time. One guy made our sandwiches and the guy who took our order made us a cannoli. Get ready cause this is the best part. Walks to the back area and grabs the cannoli, fills it with cream and sprinkles chocolate chips on top alllll with his bare unwashed hands 🙃 Even if we weren’t in the middle of a GLOBAL PANDEMIC that is sooo nasty. We then had to correct him on the price. He didn’t know the answer to any of our questions, he had to forward every question we asked to the other worker. They didn’t have the table cloths which isn’t that big of a deal but kinda just the cherry on top of a bad experience.
Great sandwiches and cannolis

BEWARE this place is cash only and the surcharge for their ATM is 3.25. As a result, with my bank charging a fee for using an out of network atm, I paid an extra five bucks for my sandwich. The sandwich was good but this practice is extortionate!!! Totally unfair to have that kind of unforeseen surcharge!!! Never even had an atm that expensive in my dang life ! You can at least add CASH ONLY on this site so that people know ahead of time!
This a very small place to eat an delicios italian sandwich
Greaaaat sandwiches!!!!!

This review is called - I should have gone to Jimmy John's!  Have you ever been excited to try a new place? Well that was me an hour ago. That is NOT ME NOW!  The lady at the counter was HORRENDOUSLY RUDE! I ordered a quick meal through Uber Eats. I was excited to try their Koolaid but found out it's no longer available. I decided I would buy 3 drinks. She rang up my sodas and I pulled out my credit card. She SCREAMED - CASH ONLY?!? There were no signs that I saw. Ok though. How about you make a sale by saying "Hey we don't accept credit cards but if you'd like place an order through Uber Eats for the items and you will be good to go."  Long story short - DONT WASTE YOUR TIME HERE! Also the cannoli that I ordered was not "piped when I ordered it" It felt cold and sad :(  Just steer clear of this place. It's just not worth it!
Omg, one of the best sandwiches, plenty of great meat and toppings and giardiniera is hot...a must try in logan Square...

Pretty good meatballs with sauce and provolone.  Unfortunately nobody that worked there was wearing a mask.  First restaurant I've been to during the pandemic without seeing any masks.  Come on guys it's a pandemic.

Completely disappointed. I was excited to try this place but how can I be expected to help a local biz that doesn't give you any food for $14? Cheap on the meat, paid over $12 for Italian classic plus, meat doesn't even weigh out to 2 ounces. tasted only bread and balsamic. Probably not coming back.
minestrone soup had no flavor. the italian deluxe sandwich was okay- lacked meat. however, the bread is outstanding. i'll give it another try, but would like to see more meat on the deli sandwiches.
Love these subs! Never disappointed.
Great food and great service. Plus they have Kool  Ade! Angel was amazing and took great care of my friends and I!
Best tuna sandwich ove ever had!
small portions and over priced
Awesome  joint first a  Sandwich
Classic Italian, mostly bread and lettuce.
Sandwiches were great, but it is cash only.
Keto bowl was perfect
Always amazing sandwiches. Great job guys.

What service! I breezed right past the sign on the door saying it was cash only, and didn't realize until it was too late. I didn't have a debit card, and they let me leave with my lunch under the honor system that i'd return to pay someday (which I did later that day). The employees were very proud to work there and raved about the food and the owner. To top it off, the sammy and soup were deelish. Can't beat service like this place. Excited to come back for the muffuletta!
They are tight on the amount of ingredients you get, yes the cheese and bread are great. it's very expensive too... 9.95 for an 8 inch sub...
Good sandwhich. The guy running the joint was helpful and went over customer favorites. Would return.

OUTSTANDING eggplant parmigiana sandwich! It was gone before I could take a picture.  LOL. Seriously,  get it and add giardinera.  So delicious! Same owners as Sicilia Bakery in Jefferson Park.  Great sauce,  fresh bread and perfectly baked eggplant with just the right amount of mozzarella make this sandwich 5 stars!
This place is small and if you aren't looking for it you will pass by without knowing. I love their sandwiches and Paninis so much. Delicious, fresh, friendly owner, i recommend it 100%!
Low key spot with delicious sandwiches. Multiple flavors of Kool-aid with cane sugar? Yes please!

Stopped by to finally get the special muffulatte sandwich. Mama Mia!!! Delish isn't a strong enough word for this masterpiece.... A Big shout out to Neil for preparing it for me... I will be back soon. A must try.

The veggie sandwich I had today literally melted  in my mouth! Red marinated peppers , artichokes and melted cheese and more .... delicious !  They made handmade cannolis fresh for me w chocolate and choice of pistachios or choc chips while I waited for my sandwich . Now tell me what Italian sandwich shop does that anymore ?!! Zowie
Amazing tuna sandwich! Fast, friendly service. Dirty Chips. 5 stars.
Love their vegetarian friendly option with the pesto. Very filling. Wish they took credit cards but otherwise this place is awesome.

Wow I am so excited I found this new Diamonds in the Rough in Logan Square. I had the suits yesterday on such a cold day and I have to say while to the whoever is making the homemade soups. And the meatball beef combo with the hot Jordan Air and the marinara sauce now I know why they call it the couch. After eating it me and the cops became best friends. The staff was polite the food was made fresh oh, and I would definitely go back without any hesitation. The neighborhood so needed a spot like this to go to.
Joe says yes!
Cash only, great food! Hot or cold can't go wrong
Definitely worth checking out! I've tried the Italian Beef and Minestrone soup, both were very very good. The staff has always been friendly! The Italian cookies were also really tasty!

Aug 31 2018. I was hanging in the neighborhood for the day. A guy up at Galerie F recommended this place when I asked for a solid local sandwich. I was not disappointed. Loved it. I was the only person in there when in ordered. Took a little longer than I expected, but that’s no problem when a sandwich is this good (had some Italian sandwich). Highly recommended.
Quick and good
Hot sandwiches are great! Best beef in the neighborhood.

This place is great! Smaller menu of well crafted sandwiches. Had the meatball sub and it was enough for my fiance and I to share. They also do picnic baskets which is a great idea for a group outing. The owners are very nice and the dirty chips are delicious. Will be back soon.

I Bought the eggplant farm sandwich and I have to say the hype is REAL! I'm proud to say I will be a regular at this establishment from now on. The customer service is at par with the quality of the food i just devoured.A+++++
So close to my house. The sandwiches are amazing and the koolade brings you back to your childhood. The staff there are amazing. I hope this place stays for a long long time!
Love the hot sandwiches and the desserts far more than the cold sandwiches, highly recommend the Meatballs with Spicy Peppers
Great New sandwich shop! Tiny joint in Logan square pumping out quality food. I would have included a photo of my excellent Italian beef but I ate it that damn fast. Simple menu done well.
Awesome service and awesome sandwiches.

Fantastic mom and pop sandwich spot! Was greeted immideatly after entering by who I think my have been the owner. I'm on a strict diet so my options are limited while eating out, but I ended up getting an Italian beef no bread. While he was making it, he explained how he was layering all the cheese and giardinara so it's mixed well, and not just thrown in the bowl. Great guy and the beef is very tasty. Will be back and will bring my wife and kid along too

Great meatball sanwhiches. Bread had a nice bite on the outside and sublime sotness on the inside.   My 9 year old loved it.   She declared it the best she's had.   You know kids palates are more sensitive.   If she has no objections than neither will you.
Best italian sangwich of my life (so far). I plan on eating this until I die.  2018 is pretty good I guess now.
Good so good!

Drove past this place a few times, but I’m glad I finally went in. I was super hungry and got “The Trifecta”, put it inside of my face, and now my lil belly is full. It was a little messy, so I would advise against eating if you’re wearing a tuxedo.  I’m excited to try some of the other menu items, the veggie looks very good and had some thought put into it—it’s not just a turkey sub minus the turkey.

Was very excited to have a new sandwich shop in the neighborhood.  I need to preface with the fact that they just opened last week and they're just getting going, but I'm a big fan of Bari on Grand and was a big fan of Hero's on Western until they closed.  I have to say it was a lot of bread and not a lot of meat...  If you care to compare, a 12 inch at Bari is less than the 8 inch here and it seems like Bari's is more than twice the meat and cheese for less money.  I will definitely give them another shot.  It wasn't at all bad, but I wasn't super impressed on my first impression.

Great new sandwich spot in Logan Square! They menu is pretty simple- they stick to just a few sandwiches, but they all looked great! We had an Italian, Italian Deluxe, and a Egg Plant Parm... not a crumb was left. The get their bread delivered from a local bakery, so it is really good and fresh.  They had only been open for a few days and ran out of bread right after we were there, so make sure you go early... or you will have to wait while more bread gets delivered! Not sure if that is a bad thing or just means everything they sell is SUPER fresh!
